Package: forestIPM
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Hierarchical Integral Projection Model for Tree Population Dynamics
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Willian", "Vieira", , "willian.vieira@usherbrooke.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Integral Projection Model for studying tree population dynamics
    (population growth rates, coexistence, sensitivity) in eastern North America.
    Uses Bayesian hierarchical vital rate models parameterized from forest inventory data.
